The major features in which our species differ from the known
Dasyblatta
(
D. charpentierae Bonfils, 1975
;
D. stylata , Bonfils, 1975
;
D. chopardi Hebard, 1921
;
D. thaumasia , Hebard, 1921
;
D. maldonadoi Rocha E Silva Albuquerque, 1964
;
D. vogli Princis, 1955
;
D. melanocephala , Princis, 1955
) are: immaculate pronotum, styles only slightly curved, ocelli absent, subgenital plate not strongly asymmetrical, tergite anterior to supra-anal plate symmetrical, supra-anal plate trapezoidal. We suspect this species is not closely related to any of the known
Dasyblatta
.
